wikipedia_page.main: Sir John Thomas Banks   (14 October 1816 – 16 July 1908) was an Anglo-Irish physician and, between 1880 and 1898, Regius Professor of Physic at Trinity College, Dublin.

In 1898, he succeeded Sir John Banks, K.C.B., as Regius Professor of Physic in the University of Dublin, retaining this office until his death, taking a prominent part in the conduct of the Final Examinations in Medicine.

Hume built a number of houses. In 1770, he built number 5 Ely Row (previously Hume Row).McCready, C.T. (1892) Dublin Street Names, Dated and Explained. Dublin: Hodges, Figgis, & Co. p. 52. He built a mansion in Merrion Square, east, which was later divided into two large houses, in one of which Sir John Banks, physician to Queen Victoria, lived.
